622
00:41:28.285 --> 00:41:30.735
I know why you lied for her.

623
00:41:31.550 --> 00:41:35.006
I'd have done the same
thing to protect Tara.

624
00:41:37.796 --> 00:41:39.581
Does Gemma know?

625
00:41:40.028 --> 00:41:41.154
Yeah.

626
00:41:43.251 --> 00:41:45.516
Tara's cut her out.

627
00:41:46.154 --> 00:41:48.885
She's dead to my family.

628
00:41:50.978 --> 00:41:52.503
Shit.

629
00:41:55.588 --> 00:41:58.236
You're the only thing she's got left.

630
00:42:00.176 --> 00:42:01.743
She don't want me.

631
00:42:06.795 --> 00:42:08.979
I'm worried about her. Clay.

632
00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:12.268
She's already on edge.

633
00:42:13.052 --> 00:42:16.291
I'm not sure what happens
to her without family.

634
00:42:23.586 --> 00:42:26.044
She's gonna need you.

635
00:42:44.983 --> 00:42:46.862
Somebody to see you. babe.

636
00:42:57.153 --> 00:42:58.285
We okay here?

637
00:42:59.085 --> 00:43:00.293
Yeah.

638
00:43:02.003 --> 00:43:04.341
- I heard what you said.
- Good.

639
00:43:06.063 --> 00:43:07.594
Be civil.

640
00:43:13.876 --> 00:43:15.558
I didn't feel like going home.

641
00:43:24.338 --> 00:43:26.698
You want to fix the damage you've done?

642
00:43:27.329 --> 00:43:30.552
Yes. Of course I do.

643
00:43:30.748 --> 00:43:34.305
Then you need to prove to
Tara that you can be trusted.

644
00:43:34.419 --> 00:43:36.285
I'm cold turkey. Jax.

645
00:43:36.407 --> 00:43:38.407
No booze. no weed.

646
00:43:38.531 --> 00:43:39.880
